Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
LIVE . WORK . SHOP . PLAY.

Just to the west of Omaha’s city center, a metamorphosis is taking place. A complete reimagining of what a “surban” (suburban meets urban) development can be. With nearly 500 acres of mixed-use, pedestrian-friendly space, Heartwood Preserve will become the cornerstone for gathering, living, working, shopping, and playing in Omaha. And at the core of its being is the integration and protection of the natural beauty of the region.
